snippet: By 2016, Democrats’ stretch of presidential advantage will have lasted 24 years, and one of the biggest questions in American politics is how close Republicans are to ending it.
abstract: Political Memo; big question in American politics is how close Republicans are to replicating Democrats’ process of rejuvenation and winning the White House again; Democrats have won popular vote in five of the six last elections; Republicans are contemplating tinkering with their nomination process, something Democrats tried with little success.
lead_paragraph: By 2016, Democrats’ stretch of presidential advantage will have lasted 24 years, and one of the biggest questions in American politics is how close Republicans are to ending it.

headline.main: Shut Out of White House, G.O.P. Looks to Democrats of 1992
headline.print_headline: Shut Out of White House, G.O.P. Looks to Democrats of 1992
